	ages 0-18 months and their families can enjoy stories\, songs\, and fun le
	arning activities.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nSouthwest Branch\n\nRoom Location:
	 Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nD
	etailed Description: Early Learning is a great way for babies and their fa
	milies to develop learning\, literacy\, and language skills as well as com
	munity with other families.\, We read stories\, sing songs\, and have enga
	ging\, educational activities that help kids and their caregivers grow tog
	ether.\n\nEvent Logistics: Registration is not required but these programs
	 are very popular and the room capacity can fill up quickly.\, \, Families
	 of all ages are welcome\, though this early learning program is intended 
	for youth aged 0-18 months\, their caregivers and families.\, Find out mor
	e about\n\nEarly Learning & Story Time\n\nprograms.\n\nContact Us: If you 
	have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nAD
	A Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabiliti
	es at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before 
	the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and o
	pen to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/baby-s
	tory-time/17650240/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
